# dbf880601c2348ccb736cc66574a4c53
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1383
msgid "Added ``dependency_links`` to allow specifying URLs for ``--find-links``."
msgstr ""

# 1b51baf21bef4f1aa2705235014145dd
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1385
msgid ""
"Enhanced test loader to scan packages as well as modules, and call "
"``additional_tests()`` if present to get non-unittest tests."
msgstr ""

# e4595b83bc684a50972689e899aa2f7e
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1388
msgid ""
"Support namespace packages in conjunction with system packagers, by "
"omitting the installation of any ``__init__.py`` files for namespace "
"packages, and adding a special ``.pth`` file to create a working package "
"in ``sys.modules``."
msgstr ""

# e7ab63c926824a66b05a182759ee7e07
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1393
msgid ""
"Made ``--single-version-externally-managed`` automatic when ``--root`` is"
" used, so that most system packagers won't require special support for "
"setuptools."
msgstr ""

# 69ac1e49247a43ad9f02b0053e86ee92
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1397
msgid ""
"Fixed ``setup_requires``, ``tests_require``, etc. not using ``setup.cfg``"
" or other configuration files for their option defaults when installing, "
"and also made the install use ``--multi-version`` mode so that the "
"project directory doesn't need to support .pth files."
msgstr ""

# 0eb37edf41e247df9aba2057b29e5259
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1402
msgid ""
"``MANIFEST.in`` is now forcibly closed when any errors occur while "
"reading it.  Previously, the file could be left open and the actual error"
" would be masked by problems trying to remove the open file on Windows "
"systems."
msgstr ""

# ca4de9ce43404093b83d620209b3046d
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1408
msgid "0.6a10"
msgstr ""

# af04d98ea0d6437598b410df8cbab714
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1410
msgid "Fixed the ``develop`` command ignoring ``--find-links``."
msgstr ""

# e931c63c9cca4450beff23cc2fcf7860
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1414
msgid "0.6a9"
msgstr ""

# 128849ef33164110a276baae4b83992f
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1416
msgid ""
"The ``sdist`` command no longer uses the traditional ``MANIFEST`` file to"
" create source distributions.  ``MANIFEST.in`` is still read and "
"processed, as are the standard defaults and pruning.  But the manifest is"
" built inside the project's ``.egg-info`` directory as ``SOURCES.txt``, "
"and it is rebuilt every time the ``egg_info`` command is run."
msgstr ""

# 6944204b40f84f7d8be4df2bee2ee535
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1422
msgid ""
"Added the ``include_package_data`` keyword to ``setup()``, allowing you "
"to automatically include any package data listed in revision control or "
"``MANIFEST.in``"
msgstr ""

# 0e2b0187bf8446b289d7a6b4f6a639ac
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1426
msgid ""
"Added the ``exclude_package_data`` keyword to ``setup()``, allowing you "
"to trim back files included via the ``package_data`` and "
"``include_package_data`` options."
msgstr ""

# 8018b97867814177885ec283ce1499c9
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1430
msgid ""
"Fixed ``--tag-svn-revision`` not working when run from a source "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

# 9f83b98c262c4381b91b08db653dc328
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1433
msgid "Added warning for namespace packages with missing ``declare_namespace()``"
msgstr ""

# 330b05bf83e74fd4bef2d8d0bf907123
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1435
msgid ""
"Added ``tests_require`` keyword to ``setup()``, so that e.g. packages "
"requiring ``nose`` to run unit tests can make this dependency optional "
"unless the ``test`` command is run."
msgstr ""

# 4a979fb13fe44bd98a26f3cc7554bba8
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1439
msgid ""
"Made all commands that use ``easy_install`` respect its configuration "
"options, as this was causing some problems with ``setup.py install``."
msgstr ""

# 3210f1a915434022b7cf3426eed77221
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1442
msgid ""
"Added an ``unpack_directory()`` driver to ``setuptools.archive_util``, so"
" that you can process a directory tree through a processing filter as if "
"it were a zipfile or tarfile."
msgstr ""

# dcfcb88df4004b10878f4c3bead0b5cf
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1446
msgid ""
"Added an internal ``install_egg_info`` command to use as part of old-"
"style ``install`` operations, that installs an ``.egg-info`` directory "
"with the package."
msgstr ""

# 892185051eb8413598074b93d2fcfba7
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1450
msgid ""
"Added a ``--single-version-externally-managed`` option to the ``install``"
" command so that you can more easily wrap a \"flat\" egg in a system "
"package."
msgstr ""

# 3e090007f0dd4d1f847d5fa81dcb33ef
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1453
msgid ""
"Enhanced ``bdist_rpm`` so that it installs single-version eggs that don't"
" rely on a ``.pth`` file.  The ``--no-egg`` option has been removed, "
"since all RPMs are now built in a more backwards-compatible format."
msgstr ""

# fe0ef6e3c14a4c7d9d4236a4f5fcafb6
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1457
msgid ""
"Support full roundtrip translation of eggs to and from ``bdist_wininst`` "
"format.  Running ``bdist_wininst`` on a setuptools-based package wraps "
"the egg in an .exe that will safely install it as an egg (i.e., with "
"metadata and entry-point wrapper scripts), and ``easy_install`` can turn "
"the .exe back into an ``.egg`` file or directory and install it as such."
msgstr ""

# 0b3904fc7aab47ceaef6032f7adf9801
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1466
msgid "0.6a8"
msgstr ""

# a980662e48db44f08583178799e18f05
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1468
msgid ""
"Fixed some problems building extensions when Pyrex was installed, "
"especially with Python 2.4 and/or packages using SWIG."
msgstr ""

# 4d49906b08504c5bad0dd243eba891ef
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1471
msgid ""
"Made ``develop`` command accept all the same options as ``easy_install``,"
" and use the ``easy_install`` command's configuration settings as "
"defaults."
msgstr ""

# 1b8dbe3026e749949295b317f0f3ca01
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1474
msgid ""
"Made ``egg_info --tag-svn-revision`` fall back to extracting the revision"
" number from ``PKG-INFO`` in case it is being run on a source "
"distribution of a snapshot taken from a Subversion-based project."
msgstr ""

# dbb6e16bd4d84005b45601b3b5c8e75d
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1478
msgid ""
"Automatically detect ``.dll``, ``.so`` and ``.dylib`` files that are "
"being installed as data, adding them to ``native_libs.txt`` "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

# 84434e7c9e3e463d83ae556c6ba0d84c
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1481
msgid ""
"Fixed some problems with fresh checkouts of projects that don't include "
"``.egg-info/PKG-INFO`` under revision control and put the project's "
"source code directly in the project directory.  If such a package had any"
" requirements that get processed before the ``egg_info`` command can be "
"run, the setup scripts would fail with a \"Missing 'Version:' header "
"and/or PKG-INFO file\" error, because the egg runtime interpreted the "
"unbuilt metadata in a directory on ``sys.path`` (i.e. the current "
"directory) as being a corrupted egg.  Setuptools now monkeypatches the "
"distribution metadata cache to pretend that the egg has valid version "
"information, until it has a chance to make it actually be so (via the "
"``egg_info`` command)."
msgstr ""

# f24d54e3f67046a89848c6b017c6c198
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1494
msgid "0.6a5"
msgstr ""

# 43e3469387de4e17a7d57fedf76b97d8
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1496
msgid "Fixed missing gui/cli .exe files in distribution.  Fixed bugs in tests."
msgstr ""

# e92fea5c313e42ed8e5470cb4c483db0
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1500
msgid "0.6a3"
msgstr ""

# 4a7a9cbccca34117a64ed00a4f1853ff
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1502
msgid ""
"Added ``gui_scripts`` entry point group to allow installing GUI scripts "
"on Windows and other platforms.  (The special handling is only for "
"Windows; other platforms are treated the same as for "
"``console_scripts``.)"
msgstr ""

# d420e3ba15654da883c83e7539db94cf
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1508
msgid "0.6a2"
msgstr ""

# 5e59aaf60f3244cf8eb125f745c21d4a
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1510
msgid ""
"Added ``console_scripts`` entry point group to allow installing scripts "
"without the need to create separate script files.  On Windows, console "
"scripts get an ``.exe`` wrapper so you can just type their name.  On "
"other platforms, the scripts are written without a file extension."
msgstr ""

# 59a68706b75c46e7a64cc38f4e44bd60
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1517
msgid "0.6a1"
msgstr ""

# c3711ff46ceb49448566b5fd66087218
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1519
msgid ""
"Added support for building \"old-style\" RPMs that don't install an egg "
"for the target package, using a ``--no-egg`` option."
msgstr ""

# d374f8647cc74b6c9458952d69fa1cb9
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1522
msgid ""
"The ``build_ext`` command now works better when using the ``--inplace`` "
"option and multiple Python versions.  It now makes sure that all "
"extensions match the current Python version, even if newer copies were "
"built for a different Python version."
msgstr ""

# 18a1050dd43f47189ed2ae591f76e83f
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1527
msgid ""
"The ``upload`` command no longer attaches an extra ``.zip`` when "
"uploading eggs, as PyPI now supports egg uploads without trickery."
msgstr ""

# a9ae24cf3a08460088af2c9a396eaebe
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1530
msgid ""
"The ``ez_setup`` script/module now displays a warning before downloading "
"the setuptools egg, and attempts to check the downloaded egg against an "
"internal MD5 checksum table."
msgstr ""

# 21e0a33050864a99be29230c0712d17c
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1534
msgid ""
"Fixed the ``--tag-svn-revision`` option of ``egg_info`` not finding the "
"latest revision number; it was using the revision number of the directory"
" containing ``setup.py``, not the highest revision number in the project."
msgstr ""

# a85eb59a149e4fc1bf46505b7a4f2057
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1538
msgid "Added ``eager_resources`` setup argument"
msgstr ""

# 8fc2ae7bd33a47ac8c8a1f65ad370576
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1540
msgid ""
"The ``sdist`` command now recognizes Subversion \"deleted file\" entries "
"and does not include them in source distributions."
msgstr ""

# 2e8394a9cd1443e4897d8bef3a70d03e
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1543
msgid ""
"``setuptools`` now embeds itself more thoroughly into the distutils, so "
"that other distutils extensions (e.g. py2exe, py2app) will subclass "
"setuptools' versions of things, rather than the native distutils ones."
msgstr ""

# 24e4dac0a4c642878b1108db41957ab1
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1547
msgid ""
"Added ``entry_points`` and ``setup_requires`` arguments to ``setup()``; "
"``setup_requires`` allows you to automatically find and download packages"
" that are needed in order to *build* your project (as opposed to running "
"it)."
msgstr ""

# 9e2da8b656684062b1797a605ea5bc8c
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1551
msgid ""
"``setuptools`` now finds its commands, ``setup()`` argument validators, "
"and metadata writers using entry points, so that they can be extended by "
"third-party packages.  See `Creating distutils Extensions "
"<http://pythonhosted.org/setuptools/setuptools.html#creating-distutils-"
"extensions>`_ for more details."
msgstr ""

# 5d57b9754d1d468db1fd17f734df906b
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1557
msgid ""
"The vestigial ``depends`` command has been removed.  It was never "
"finished or documented, and never would have worked without EasyInstall -"
" which it pre-dated and was never compatible with."
msgstr ""

# f620dfcef8a04886b110a088d85e073e
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1563
msgid "0.5a12"
msgstr ""

# 5bee864c67cd4b57b941b55b8031d817
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1565
msgid ""
"The zip-safety scanner now checks for modules that might be used with "
"``python -m``, and marks them as unsafe for zipping, since Python 2.4 "
"can't handle ``-m`` on zipped modules."
msgstr ""

# e56bf85696dd4fab9dc3c2c8f79d9033
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1571
msgid "0.5a11"
msgstr ""

# af1dcef621274304b2786a771727b02a
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1573
msgid ""
"Fix breakage of the \"develop\" command that was caused by the addition "
"of ``--always-unzip`` to the ``easy_install`` command."
msgstr ""

# 306349a94d80412791f214167a17da74
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1578
msgid "0.5a9"
msgstr ""

# 408f11547bb8491aafaa6595d9317496
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1580
msgid ""
"Include ``svn:externals`` directories in source distributions as well as "
"normal subversion-controlled files and directories."
msgstr ""

# 5d17ed5e2bdd4e368a7c52d989854c2f
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1583
msgid "Added ``exclude=patternlist`` option to ``setuptools.find_packages()``"
msgstr ""

# b0e2cd43ad9346dd98ce1e8330db61dd
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1585
msgid ""
"Changed --tag-svn-revision to include an \"r\" in front of the revision "
"number for better readability."
msgstr ""

# 85b075dbd44d49c4b5a7569d40a2056e
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1588
msgid ""
"Added ability to build eggs without including source files (except for "
"any scripts, of course), using the ``--exclude-source-files`` option to "
"``bdist_egg``."
msgstr ""

# 4b31e82c387a4c2396ba4e28757365f2
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1592
msgid ""
"``setup.py install`` now automatically detects when an \"unmanaged\" "
"package or module is going to be on ``sys.path`` ahead of a package being"
" installed, thereby preventing the newer version from being imported.  If"
" this occurs, a warning message is output to ``sys.stderr``, but "
"installation proceeds anyway.  The warning message informs the user what "
"files or directories need deleting, and advises them they can also use "
"EasyInstall (with the ``--delete-conflicting`` option) to do it "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

# adc23a55efba408395bd2c5accfba729
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1600
msgid ""
"The ``egg_info`` command now adds a ``top_level.txt`` file to the "
"metadata directory that lists all top-level modules and packages in the "
"distribution. This is used by the ``easy_install`` command to find "
"possibly-conflicting \"unmanaged\" packages when installing the "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

# e84e8bbb07e6498f8dedf71b4fb4f7a8
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1605
msgid ""
"Added ``zip_safe`` and ``namespace_packages`` arguments to ``setup()``. "
"Added package analysis to determine zip-safety if the ``zip_safe`` flag "
"is not given, and advise the author regarding what code might need "
"changing."
msgstr ""

# edb6dd8335e442dfae24d01d428f8512
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1609
msgid "Fixed the swapped ``-d`` and ``-b`` options of ``bdist_egg``."
msgstr ""

# 3ce20c59166543f69c471101cd16260d
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1613
msgid "0.5a8"
msgstr ""

# 134c1dfe436a4c9fa7439c089000b79a
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1615
msgid ""
"The \"egg_info\" command now always sets the distribution metadata to "
"\"safe\" forms of the distribution name and version, so that distribution"
" files will be generated with parseable names (i.e., ones that don't "
"include '-' in the name or version).  Also, this means that if you use "
"the various ``--tag`` options of \"egg_info\", any distributions "
"generated will use the tags in the version, not just egg distributions."
msgstr ""

# 4dfdc624cbd64dc8aaf8c4073a69e819
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1622
msgid ""
"Added support for defining command aliases in distutils configuration "
"files, under the \"[aliases]\" section.  To prevent recursion and to "
"allow aliases to call the command of the same name, a given alias can be "
"expanded only once per command-line invocation.  You can define new "
"aliases with the \"alias\" command, either for the local, global, or per-"
"user configuration."
msgstr ""

# 6b037b10fdf540e69920858f6f11c831
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1628
msgid ""
"Added \"rotate\" command to delete old distribution files, given a set of"
" patterns to match and the number of files to keep.  (Keeps the most "
"recently-modified distribution files matching each pattern.)"
msgstr ""

# b6255135d1c0470a807c625e10d71e58
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1632
msgid ""
"Added \"saveopts\" command that saves all command-line options for the "
"current invocation to the local, global, or per-user configuration file."
"  Useful for setting defaults without having to hand-edit a configuration"
" file."
msgstr ""

# 8a09f2f9dfc347c7b60b1105eb9bf237
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1636
msgid ""
"Added a \"setopt\" command that sets a single option in a specified "
"distutils configuration file."
msgstr ""

# 6e8e3576be464e1988f14fbd3933efc8
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1641
msgid "0.5a7"
msgstr ""

# 7082013905524abf8be0b252096cb76f
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1643
msgid ""
"Added \"upload\" support for egg and source distributions, including a "
"bug fix for \"upload\" and a temporary workaround for lack of .egg "
"support in PyPI."
msgstr ""

# e79b3ec0c16d4ae492568c85630a0455
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1649
msgid "0.5a6"
msgstr ""

# 957624ee1e6d41dab5aa2981a2c68cd2
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1651
msgid ""
"Beefed up the \"sdist\" command so that if you don't have a MANIFEST.in, "
"it will include all files under revision control (CVS or Subversion) in "
"the current directory, and it will regenerate the list every time you "
"create a source distribution, not just when you tell it to.  This should "
"make the default \"do what you mean\" more often than the distutils' "
"default behavior did, while still retaining the old behavior in the "
"presence of MANIFEST.in."
msgstr ""

# f8dc47ee3f91468bb6271aabf01ccbcc
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1658
msgid ""
"Fixed the \"develop\" command always updating .pth files, even if you "
"specified ``-n`` or ``--dry-run``."
msgstr ""

# 397593ded2ac44a793e2a6a6de1d2d17
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1661
msgid ""
"Slightly changed the format of the generated version when you use "
"``--tag-build`` on the \"egg_info\" command, so that you can make tagged "
"revisions compare *lower* than the version specified in setup.py (e.g. by"
" using ``--tag-build=dev``)."
msgstr ""

# 2425702e047e41af97d585858205c45a
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1668
msgid "0.5a5"
msgstr ""

# e4ee7d829e3041b5a62ad80ed97421c0
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1670
msgid ""
"Added ``develop`` command to ``setuptools``-based packages.  This command"
" installs an ``.egg-link`` pointing to the package's source directory, "
"and script wrappers that ``execfile()`` the source versions of the "
"package's scripts.  This lets you put your development checkout(s) on "
"sys.path without having to actually install them.  (To uninstall the "
"link, use use ``setup.py develop --uninstall``.)"
msgstr ""

# 373bde62e8f04dc3a72c25bfb04d15e5
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1677
msgid ""
"Added ``egg_info`` command to ``setuptools``-based packages.  This "
"command just creates or updates the \"projectname.egg-info\" directory, "
"without building an egg.  (It's used by the ``bdist_egg``, ``test``, and "
"``develop`` commands.)"
msgstr ""

# fa57cd8dbf33432598c0de8c78e43dd8
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1682
msgid ""
"Enhanced the ``test`` command so that it doesn't install the package, but"
" instead builds any C extensions in-place, updates the ``.egg-info`` "
"metadata, adds the source directory to ``sys.path``, and runs the tests "
"directly on the source.  This avoids an \"unmanaged\" installation of the"
" package to ``site-packages`` or elsewhere."
msgstr ""

# f1ec65814b84448db5b6cc9ba7d0def0
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1688
msgid ""
"Made ``easy_install`` a standard ``setuptools`` command, moving it from "
"the ``easy_install`` module to ``setuptools.command.easy_install``.  Note"
" that if you were importing or extending it, you must now change your "
"imports accordingly.  ``easy_install.py`` is still installed as a script,"
" but not as a module."
msgstr ""

# 9cc414867c734b5a8729a1d58def08ef
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1696
msgid "0.5a4"
msgstr ""

# 11a7fe56dc8443119cf7ed1144c00690
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1698
msgid ""
"Setup scripts using setuptools can now list their dependencies directly "
"in the setup.py file, without having to manually create a ``depends.txt``"
" file. The ``install_requires`` and ``extras_require`` arguments to "
"``setup()`` are used to create a dependencies file automatically.  If you"
" are manually creating ``depends.txt`` right now, please switch to using "
"these setup arguments as soon as practical, because ``depends.txt`` "
"support will be removed in the 0.6 release cycle.  For documentation on "
"the new arguments, see the ``setuptools.dist.Distribution`` class."
msgstr ""

# c25d74174ba94351afff6ad16cba9b9c
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1707
msgid ""
"Setup scripts using setuptools now always install using ``easy_install`` "
"internally, for ease of uninstallation and upgrading."
msgstr ""

# c838538602d148e2a281112595802a81
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1712
msgid "0.5a1"
msgstr ""

# 4cc722468b6e4bd3bec8d467f213e4f4
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1714
msgid ""
"Added support for \"self-installation\" bootstrapping.  Packages can now "
"include ``ez_setup.py`` in their source distribution, and add the "
"following to their ``setup.py``, in order to automatically bootstrap "
"installation of setuptools as part of their setup process::"
msgstr ""

# 8fe8db8b98ba409f997a7bf909de8c50
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1727
msgid "0.4a2"
msgstr ""

# 49257e174ed04d4f80ab1cb1d644de3c
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1729
msgid ""
"Added ``ez_setup.py`` installer/bootstrap script to make initial "
"setuptools installation easier, and to allow distributions using "
"setuptools to avoid having to include setuptools in their source "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

# a0a2d9d712e24b8285764037c4560d92
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1733
msgid ""
"All downloads are now managed by the ``PackageIndex`` class (which is now"
" subclassable and replaceable), so that embedders can more easily "
"override download logic, give download progress reports, etc.  The class "
"has also been moved to the new ``setuptools.package_index`` module."
msgstr ""

# fea156d3da104a09a0a22f5a8406c0cb
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1738
msgid ""
"The ``Installer`` class no longer handles downloading, manages a "
"temporary directory, or tracks the ``zip_ok`` option.  Downloading is now"
" handled by ``PackageIndex``, and ``Installer`` has become an "
"``easy_install`` command class based on ``setuptools.Command``."
msgstr ""

# 1f9c161db72f492887129194550dfb17
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1743
msgid ""
"There is a new ``setuptools.sandbox.run_setup()`` API to invoke a setup "
"script in a directory sandbox, and a new ``setuptools.archive_util`` "
"module with an ``unpack_archive()`` API.  These were split out of "
"EasyInstall to allow reuse by other tools and applications."
msgstr ""

# a744837bfd024fc6850ee7b331ec7daf
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1748
msgid ""
"``setuptools.Command`` now supports reinitializing commands using keyword"
" arguments to set/reset options.  Also, ``Command`` subclasses can now "
"set their ``command_consumes_arguments`` attribute to ``True`` in order "
"to receive an ``args`` option containing the rest of the command line."
msgstr ""

# b5cdab7f32aa407c8565c831e8dcb672
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1755
msgid "0.3a2"
msgstr ""

# 474240d63d2c48da941040bdc66b4b6b
#: ../../venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-2.2.dist-info/DESCRIPTION.rst:1757
msgid ""
"Added new options to ``bdist_egg`` to allow tagging the egg's version "
"number with a subversion revision number, the current date, or an "
"explicit tag value.  Run ``setup.py bdist_egg --help`` to get more "
"information."
msgstr ""

